OL,3,CWalsall residents heartbroken after
OL,4,Csewage flooded their homes
OL,6,FSevern Trent says it will continue to
OL,7,Finvestigate and speak with residents
OL,8,Fdirectly to find the root cause of the
OL,9,Fflooding.
OL,11,FThey are also planning to be out on
OL,12,Fthe streets in Willenhall, offering
OL,13,Fsupport to homes impacted by the
OL,14,Ffloods on Wednesday 16 October.
OL,16,FIn a statement, Michael Keenan,
OL,17,FNetwork Operations Lead at Severn
OL,18,FTrent, said: "We know how distressing
OL,19,Fany form of flooding can be and we are
OL,20,Fvery sorry to the residents of
OL,21,FFarmbridge Close and Grenville Close.
